genresAdvancedInfo.name: chaotic black metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A subgenre of heavy metal that is known for its aggressive, dissonant sound and dark, often violent lyrics. Chaotic black metal often features fast, complex guitar riffs, blast beats, and guttural vocals. The music is designed to be intense and confrontational, and is often associated with themes of nihilism, Satanism, and anti-religious sentiment.
